f, and hear Wujec’s surprising insights from watching thousands of people draw toast.\\n\\nTEDTalks is a daily video podcast of the best talks and performances from the TED Conference, where the world''s leading thinkers and doers give the talk of their lives in 18 minutes (or less). Look for talks on Technology, Entertainment and Design -- plus science, business, global issues, the arts and much more.\\nFind closed captions and translated subtitles in many languages at http://www.ted.com/translate\\n\\nFollow TED news on Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/tednews\\nLike TED on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/TED\\n\\nSubscribe to our channel: http://www.youtube.com/user/TEDtalksDirector","type":"plain"},"media$keywords":{},"media$player":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_vS_b7cJn2A&feature=youtube_gdata_player"}],"media$thumbnail":[{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_vS_b7cJn2A/0.jpg","height":360,"width":480,"time":"00:04:33"},{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_vS_b7cJn2A/1.jpg","height":90,"width":120,"time":"00:02:16.500"},{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_vS_b7cJn2A/2.jpg","height":90,"width":120,"time":"00:04:33"},{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_vS_b7cJn2A/3.jpg","height":90,"width":120,"time":"00:06:49.500"}],"media$title":{"$t":"Tom Wujec: Got a wicked problem? First, tell me how you make toast","type":"plain"},"yt$duration":{"seconds":"546"}},"gd$rating":{"average":4.877966,"max":5,"min":1,"numRaters":590,"rel":"http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#overall"},"yt$statistics":{"favoriteCount":"0","viewCount":"10419"}},{"id":{"$t":"http://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/videos/ce31WjiVcY0"},"published":{"$t":"2015-02-04T16:54:03.000Z"},"updated":{"$t":"2015-02-06T04:51:12.000Z"},"category":[{"scheme":"http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#kind","term":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007#video"},{"scheme":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007/categories.cat","term":"Tech","label":"Science & Technology"}],"title":{"$t":"Ben Ambridge: 10 myths about psychology: Debunked","type":"text"},"content":{"$t":"How much of what you think about your brain is actually wrong? In this whistlestop tour of dis-proved science, Ben Ambridge walks through 10 popular ideas about psychology that have been proven wrong — and uncovers a few surprising truths about how our brains really work.\\n\\nTEDTalks is a daily video podcast of the best talks and performances from the TED Conference, where the world''s leading thinkers and doers give the talk of their lives in 18 minutes (or less). Look for talks on Technology, Entertainment and Design -- plus science, business, global issues, the arts and much more.\\nFind closed captions and translated subtitles in many languages at http://www.ted.com/talks/ben_ambridge_10_myths_about_psychology_debunked\\n\\nFollow TED news on Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/tednews\\nLike TED on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/TED\\n\\nSubscribe to our channel: http://www.youtube.com/user/TEDtalksDirector","type":"text"},"link":[{"rel":"alternate","type":"text/html","href":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ce31WjiVcY0&feature=youtube_gdata"},{"rel":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007#video.related","type":"application/atom+xml","href":"https://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/videos/ce31WjiVcY0/related"},{"rel":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007#mobile","type":"text/html","href":"https://m.youtube.com/details?v=ce31WjiVcY0"},{"rel":"self","type":"application/atom+xml","href":"https://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/users/TEDtalksDirector/uploads/ce31WjiVcY0"}],"author":[{"name":{"$t":"TED"},"uri":{"$t":"https://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/users/TEDtalksDirector"}}],"gd$comments":{"gd$feedLink":{"rel":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007#comments","href":"https://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/videos/ce31WjiVcY0/comments","countHint":202}},"yt$hd":{},"media$group":{"media$category":[{"$t":"Tech","label":"Science & Technology","scheme":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007/categories.cat"}],"media$content":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/v/ce31WjiVcY0?version=3&f=user_uploads&app=youtube_gdata","type":"application/x-shockwave-flash","medium":"video","isDefault":"true","expression":"full","duration":900,"yt$format":5},{"url":"rtsp://r7---sn-p5qlsu7d.c.youtube.com/CigLENy73wIaHwmNcZU4WvXtcRMYDSANFEgGUgx1c2VyX3VwbG9hZHMM/0/0/0/video.3gp","type":"video/3gpp","medium":"video","expression":"full","duration":900,"yt$format":1},{"url":"rtsp://r7---sn-p5qlsu7d.c.youtube.com/CigLENy73wIaHwmNcZU4WvXtcRMYESARFEgGUgx1c2VyX3VwbG9hZHMM/0/0/0/video.3gp","type":"video/3gpp","medium":"video","expression":"full","duration":900,"yt$format":6}],"media$description":{"$t":"How much of what you think about your brain is actually wrong? In this whistlestop tour of dis-proved science, Ben Ambridge walks through 10 popular ideas about psychology that have been proven wrong — and uncovers a few surprising truths about how our brains really work.\\n\\nTEDTalks is a daily video podcast of the best talks and performances from the TED Conference, where the world''s leading thinkers and doers give the talk of their lives in 18 minutes (or less). Look for talks on Technology, Entertainment and Design -- plus science, business, global issues, the arts and much more.\\nFind closed captions and translated subtitles in many languages at http://www.ted.com/talks/ben_ambridge_10_myths_about_psychology_debunked\\n\\nFollow TED news on Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/tednews\\nLike TED on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/TED\\n\\nSubscribe to our channel: http://www.youtube.com/user/TEDtalksDirector","type":"plain"},"media$keywords":{},"media$player":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ce31WjiVcY0&feature=youtube_gdata_player"}],"media$thumbnail":[{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ce31WjiVcY0/0.jpg","height":360,"width":480,"time":"00:07:30"},{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ce31WjiVcY0/1.jpg","height":90,"width":120,"time":"00:03:45"},{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ce31WjiVcY0/2.jpg","height":90,"width":120,"time":"00:07:30"},{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/ce31WjiVcY0/3.jpg","height":90,"width":120,"time":"00:11:15"}],"media$title":{"$t":"Ben Ambridge: 10 myths about psychology: Debunked","type":"plain"},"yt$duration":{"seconds":"900"}},"gd$rating":{"average":4.5543175,"max":5,"min":1,"numRaters":1077,"rel":"http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#overall"},"yt$statistics":{"favoriteCount":"0","viewCount":"38039"}},{"id":{"$t":"http://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/videos/m048uAa8L3k"},"published":{"$t":"2015-02-03T16:22:00.000Z"},"updated":{"$t":"2015-02-06T03:05:18.000Z"},"category":[{"scheme":"http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#kind","term":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007#video"},{"scheme":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007/categories.cat","term":"Tech","label":"Science & Technology"}],"title":{"$t":"Bruce Aylward: Humanity vs. Ebola. The winning strategies in a terrifying war","type":"text"},"content":{"$t":"“Ebola threatens everything that makes us human,” says Bruce Aylward of the World Health Organization. With calm measure, he walks us through how the Ebola epidemic exploded — and how international alarm only fed the exponential growth of the problem. He shares four strategies critical to beating Ebola — and how they are succeeding, starting in Lofa County, Liberia, which was at the center of the outbreak but where no new case has been registered in weeks. The fight against Ebola is not won, he underscores, but if we do things right, we can look optimistically at our ability to fight back against epidemics. \\n\\nTEDTalks is a daily video podcast of the best talks and performances from the TED Conference, where the world''s leading thinkers and doers give the talk of their lives in 18 minutes (or less). Look for talks on Technology, Entertainment and Design -- plus science, business, global issues, the arts and much more.\\nFind closed captions and translated subtitles in many languages at http://www.ted.com/talks/bruce_aylward_humanity_vs_ebola_the_winning_strategies_in_a_terrifying_war\\n\\nFollow TED news on Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/tednews\\nLike TED on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/TED\\n\\nSubscribe to our channel: http://www.youtube.com/user/TEDtalksDirector","type":"text"},"link":[{"rel":"alternate","type":"text/html","href":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m048uAa8L3k&feature=youtube_gdata"},{"rel":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007#video.related","type":"application/atom+xml","href":"https://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/videos/m048uAa8L3k/related"},{"rel":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007#mobile","type":"text/html","href":"https://m.youtube.com/details?v=m048uAa8L3k"},{"rel":"self","type":"application/atom+xml","href":"https://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/users/TEDtalksDirector/uploads/m048uAa8L3k"}],"author":[{"name":{"$t":"TED"},"uri":{"$t":"https://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/users/TEDtalksDirector"}}],"gd$comments":{"gd$feedLink":{"rel":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007#comments","href":"https://gdata.youtube.com/feeds/api/videos/m048uAa8L3k/comments","countHint":49}},"yt$hd":{},"media$group":{"media$category":[{"$t":"Tech","label":"Science & Technology","scheme":"http://gdata.youtube.com/schemas/2007/categories.cat"}],"media$content":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/v/m048uAa8L3k?version=3&f=user_uploads&app=youtube_gdata","type":"application/x-shockwave-flash","medium":"video","isDefault":"true","expression":"full","duration":1155,"yt$format":5},{"url":"rtsp://r4---sn-p5qlsu7l.c.youtube.com/CigLENy73wIaHwl5L7wGuDxOmxMYDSANFEgGUgx1c2VyX3VwbG9hZHMM/0/0/0/video.3gp","type":"video/3gpp","medium":"video","expression":"full","duration":1155,"yt$format":1},{"url":"rtsp://r4---sn-p5qlsu7l.c.youtube.com/CigLENy73wIaHwl5L7wGuDxOmxMYESARFEgGUgx1c2VyX3VwbG9hZHMM/0/0/0/video.3gp","type":"video/3gpp","medium":"video","expression":"full","duration":1155,"yt$format":6}],"media$description":{"$t":"“Ebola threatens everything that makes us human,” says Bruce Aylward of the World Health Organization. With calm measure, he walks us through how the Ebola epidemic exploded — and how international alarm only fed the exponential growth of the problem. He shares four strategies critical to beating Ebola — and how they are succeeding, starting in Lofa County, Liberia, which was at the center of the outbreak but where no new case has been registered in weeks. The fight against Ebola is not won, he underscores, but if we do things right, we can look optimistically at our ability to fight back against epidemics. \\n\\nTEDTalks is a daily video podcast of the best talks and performances from the TED Conference, where the world''s leading thinkers and doers give the talk of their lives in 18 minutes (or less). Look for talks on Technology, Entertainment and Design -- plus science, business, global issues, the arts and much more.\\nFind closed captions and translated subtitles in many languages at http://www.ted.com/talks/bruce_aylward_humanity_vs_ebola_the_winning_strategies_in_a_terrifying_war\\n\\nFollow TED news on Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/tednews\\nLike TED on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/TED\\n\\nSubscribe to our channel: http://www.youtube.com/user/TEDtalksDirector","type":"plain"},"media$keywords":{},"media$player":[{"url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m048uAa8L3k&feature=youtube_gdata_player"}],"media$thumbnail":[{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m048uAa8L3k/0.jpg","height":360,"width":480,"time":"00:09:37.500"},{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m048uAa8L3k/1.jpg","height":90,"width":120,"time":"00:04:48.750"},{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m048uAa8L3k/2.jpg","height":90,"width":120,"time":"00:09:37.500"},{"url":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/m048uAa8L3k/3.jpg","height":90,"width":120,"time":"00:14:26.250"}],"media$title":{"$t":"Bruce Aylward: Humanity vs. Ebola. The winning strategies in a terrifying war","type":"plain"},"yt$duration":{"seconds":"1155"}},"gd$rating":{"average":4.5789475,"max":5,"min":1,"numRaters":228,"rel":"http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#overall"},"yt$statistics":{